<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="172" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="11.[153,1360,301,574]" pageId="11" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[155,521,301,334]" pageId="11" pageNumber="172">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Least Shrew 
<taxonomicName box="[344,442,340,373]" class="Mammalia" family="Tenrecidae" genus="Tenrec" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="11" pageNumber="172" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Tenrec</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed and occurs in several protected areas. It uses some disturbed habitats, including urban rice fields. Its overall population appears to be stable, but 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Major" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[477,560,419,452]" class="Mammalia" family="Tenrecidae" genus="Microgale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Afrosoricida" pageId="11" pageNumber="172" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">major</taxonomicName>
threats could be habitat degradation and use offire for forest clearing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
